The Nigerian, First Lady, Aisha Buhari, on Thursday announced that her daughter who has been in quarantine since she returned from the UK had been reunited with the family. Mrs. Buhari, who made this statement via her twitter handle, also wished all those infected with Coronavirus speedy recovery. The President’s daughter had gone into self-quarantine upon her arrival from the UK 14 days ago. The first lady expressed gratitude to God for the reunion of her daughter with the family and also prayed that the pandemic would end soon. She said, “It is a thing of joy & gratitude to Almighty God to reunite with my daughter after she had been in isolation for 14 days immediately she landed in Nigeria. “While I’m wishing all those infected for a speedy recovery, I pray for the end of this pandemic. #AbujaScaleUp”